  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] And March 8 we came to a place.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "On one side was a forest.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "On the other side was a big barn.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "There was a-- a wooden barn, a long one.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And on the side of the barn were like from stoneware also up on the barn or whatever.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "Now we stood there for a while and they were debating our-- our SS and the SS on the women.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And we already thought they're going to bring us into the forest and shoot us all, but they were-- we were like 700, 800 people, and they were only like 20 guards, or maybe 25, 30 guards.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we got together, and we decided being in that last camp, where we already-- we already couldn't go to work in Danzig.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They took us once to a railroad derailed, some wagons derailed.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they put us there to put the wagons back on the rails.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They were all-- the wagons were all filled with-- with packages and suitcases, Germans who were going back to Germany already, because they were afraid that the Russians-- the Russians, you know, coming back, coming in.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So they had a lot of suitcases, and you know, a lot of like people leaving homes.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We cut open every suitcase, every bag, and we found-- we found some-- some food, but we couldn't take too much with us because it would be obvious.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And we found revolvers and bullets.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So we divided between us like four or five revolvers.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So we were hiding it.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "We found ammunition in the-- in the suitcases.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And when we came to that place, to that forest, we got together, the four of us, because it was dark already.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was raining, like drizzling.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
